Q :- 1    What is jQuery?

Ans,:-  

     .  The purpose of jQuery is to make it much easier to use JavaScript on your website.
     .  jQuery is a lightweight, "write less, do more", JavaScript library.
     .  jQuery takes a lot of common tasks that require many lines of JavaScript code to 
        accomplish,    and wraps them into methods that you can call with a single line of code.
     .  There are lots of other JavaScript libraries out there, but jQuery is probably the most 
         popular, and also the most extendable.




Q :- 2   How to Apply CSS Using JQuery, How to Add Class and Remove Class in 
         Jquery, JQuery Animation?
Ans,:-
		....addClass() method...

     ..  addClass() method: It is used to add specified classes to each of the targeted elements   
         animating all style changes.
     ..  addClass() - Adds one or more classes to the selected elements.   


         				Syntax:

                               .addClass(className, [duration], [easing], [callback])



          .....   removeClass() method....

     ..    removeClass() method: It is used to remove the classes from the element while animating all
            style changes.

     ....   removeClass() - Removes one or more classes from the selected elements.




         					Syntax:

                        removeClass(className, [duration], [easing], [callback])







Q :- 3     How to create slider with animation?

Ans,:-      The jQuery animate() method is used to create custom animations.
             Syntax: $(selector).animate({params},speed,callback);
             The required params parameter defines the CSS properties to be
             
            animated.
                   The optional speed parameter specifies the duration of the
            effect.
                  It can take the following values: "slow", "fast", or
                  milliseconds.
